# Repository Structure

**Project**: Data Preprocessing (M.Sc. DSAI)

> **📖 Single Source of Truth**: For the complete and detailed repository structure, naming conventions, and workflow standards, please refer to [docs/01_repository-structure.md](../../docs/01_repository-structure.md).

## Quick Summary

**Seven learning layers** (week companions — **this repo only** — see [09_week-companion-architecture.mdc](./09_week-companion-architecture.mdc)):

All eight weeks live under `weeks/week1/` through `weeks/week8/` with step-numbered filenames:

- `01_reading-notes.md` — Theory (first-person learning journey)
- `02_examples.md` — Practice (worked scenarios)
- `03_quiz.md` — Self-assessment (original synthesis only)
- `04_notebook.ipynb` — Preprocessing experiments
- `05_model-paper.md` — Model exam papers / answers
- `06_discussion.md` — Week-scoped discussion / reflection prompts
- `07_assignment.md` — Week-scoped structured deliverables

Trimester-level extras: `weeks/assignments/` (graded assignment) and `weeks/model-papers/` (comprehensive papers).

**Not layers** (utilities only):

- **`src/`**: Reusable library code imported by notebooks
- **`tools/`**: Maintenance scripts (PowerShell, Python)

When writing or updating public-facing structure (e.g. docs/01_repository-structure.md, README), do not list or mention any internal-only paths.
